description: "One sheet (of eight) from a map of the Dutch East Indies, used in schools in the mid-19th century. Java is divided into residencies, and mountains—represented by short lines/dashes called hachures—major roads and settlements are shown. "
title: "School-kaart van Oost-Indië naar de laatste bekende verbeteringen meegedeede door het Departement van Koloniën"
